@startuml
title StateSpec API Field To Entity Field Mapping

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho

actor "API caller" as Caller

package "API contract" {
  rectangle "api StartOrder\nmethod POST\npath /v1/orders/{orderId}" as Api
  rectangle "input shape\n- tenantId\n- orderId\n- requestedStatus\n- displayName" as Request
}

package "Generated handler" {
  rectangle "canonical IR\nvalidated names and types" as IR
  rectangle "field mapping\npath params\nbody fields\nauth / tenant context" as Mapping
  rectangle "OCC transaction\nread version\nvalidate preconditions\nwrite mapped fields\ncommit" as Tx
}

package "Entity model" {
  rectangle "entity Order\nkey tenant_id\nkey order_id\ncreated_at\nupdated_at\nstatus\nstate_machine\ndisplay_name" as Entity
  rectangle "state_machine\ninitial state\nlegal transitions\nterminal states" as StateMachine
}

database "Versioned persisted state" as Store

Caller --> Api : invokes endpoint
Api --> Request : declares input
Api --> IR : lowers to semantic model
Request --> IR : contributes request fields
IR --> Mapping : generator consumes IR

Mapping --> Entity : tenantId -> tenant_id
Mapping --> Entity : orderId -> order_id
Mapping --> Entity : requestedStatus -> status
Mapping --> Entity : displayName -> display_name
Mapping --> Entity : tenant context -> ownership scope

Entity *-- StateMachine
Mapping --> Tx : applies inside transaction
Tx --> Entity : creates or updates entity state
Tx --> Store : optimistic concurrency commit

note right of Mapping
API-to-entity field mapping is generated
from canonical IR, not inferred directly
from raw .sspec text.
end note

note bottom of Entity
Entity management fields are foundational:
created_at, updated_at, status, and
state_machine participate in lifecycle
tracking and future garbage collection.
end note

@enduml
